[3] Cholera - Malawi (Nsanje District)
Dates: Thu 12 Mar 2015
Source: Malawi News Agency [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503120184.html


The country has registered 88 cases of cholera, and 2 people in Nsanje have succumbed to the outbreak. The Ministry of Health announced the development through its facebook page on Monday, 9 Mar 2015. "The affected districts are Nsanje with 78 cases and 2 deaths. Dedza has 1 case, Lilongwe has 1 case and Mwanza has reported 8 cases. These are the only districts that have reported cholera. Initially Chikhwawa was thought to have the cases but lab results turned out to be negative.

Minister of Health Dr. Jean Kalilani last Friday [6 Mar 2015] visited camps currently occupied by flood victims in Chikhwawa and Nsanje Districts to appreciate the extent of the need for health services. The camps visited were Bangula, Sorgin, Konzere and Sekeni 1. The health ministry has since urged people to always practice hygiene and use sanitary facilities to prevent further outbreak of cholera and other waterborne diseases.

[Byline: Tikondane Vega]

